Class ExtendableClassLoader

java.lang.Object
  |

        +--com.ibm.jikes.skij.util.ExtendableClassLoader
public class ExtendableClassLoader
extends ClassLoader

This class allows you to load classes from files that are not on the standard Java CLASSPATH. You can make a loader that loads from some combination of .class, .zip, or .jar files. Note: will try to use JDK 1.2 classes for JAR files. These classes are accessed reflectively to avoid verification problems in earlier JDKs.

loadClass

public Class loadClass(String className)                throws ClassNotFoundException
Requests the class loader to load a class with the specified name. The loadClass method is called by the Java Virtual Machine when a class loaded by a class loader first references another class.
Parameters:
name - the name of the desired class.
Returns:
the resulting Class, or null if it was not found.
Throws:
